description.narrative: (Tanzania): &amp;lt;!--td {border: 1px solid #ccc;}br {mso-data-placement:same-cell;}--&amp;gt;With FY 2020 funds, this activity will continue to implement social and behavioral change (SBC) interventions at multiple levels in order to create demand for and awareness of health services among Tanzanians, with a particular focus on changing behaviors surrounding maternal, newborn, and child health, family planning, malaria, HIV, tuberculosis and other emerging infectious diseases. Specifically, the activity aims to: (1) continue to improve the ability of individuals to practice healthy behaviors at the household level by developing and tailoring messages to geographic, epidemiological, and audience segments; (2) strengthen and scale up community support for health behaviors and ensure its sustainability; (3) improve systems for SBC coordination at national, regional and district levels and (4) implementation national SBC through integrated platforms developed by this activity... .
